<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1398,2035]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Crown brown. Face lower part brown, dorsad of antennal bases light brown with dark brown tinge. Gena and lora dark brown; anteclypeus mainly brownish, apex yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[894,968,1434,1459]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,436,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,426,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia fusca sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia lactata sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241681/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Figs. 
<number box="[957,968,1435,1459]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K, L). Pronotum brown. Mesoscutum and scutellum mainly brownish, lateral margin yellowish brown, basal triangles darker. Forewing hyaline with light brown tinge, broad band along costa except a subapical triangle, dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1104,1506,1531]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[319,1266,368,1519]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[302,1284,363,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Busonia micrata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia serrata sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241682/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[1088,1104,1507,1531]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
J). Mesepimeron dark brown. Legs and hind leg spinulation light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1398,2035]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Male genitalia. Pygofer with greater more than length, dorsal margin with smaller posterior lobe. Appendage of segment X slender, apex curved dorsally, hook-like, in posterior view crossing over each other. Subgenital plate narrow, with a few setae on dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[644,711,1650,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1434,175,1667]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia fusca sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[697,711,1651,1675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Connective with two arms not obviously broad, central lobe small and triangular. Style with row of sparsely distributed setae, apex pointed. Aedeagal shaft sparsely toothed medially, dorsal margin concave obviously in lateral view; aedeagal shaft broad in middle, compressed basally in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[305,382,1758,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1434,175,1667]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia fusca sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Figs. 
<number box="[369,382,1759,1783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
F, G).
</paragraph>
