<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="550" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[889,960,188,213]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Maldonado-Capriles" authorityName="Maldonado-Capriles" box="[974,1387,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albilateralis">
<emphasis box="[974,991,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1009,1146,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">albilateralis</emphasis>
Maldonado-Capriles
</taxonomicName>
has coloration similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Maldonado-Capriles" authorityName="Maldonado-Capriles" box="[468,785,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thai">
<emphasis box="[468,485,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[500,543,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="550">thai</emphasis>
Maldonado-Capriles
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the following characters: (
<number box="[291,303,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="550" value="1.0">1</number>
) pronotum not unicolorous, lateral margin often yellow; (
<number box="[968,983,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="550" value="2.0">2</number>
) aedeagus and gonopore comparatively narrow; (
<number box="[254,268,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="550" value="3.0">3</number>
) aedeagus dorsal margin with large process, rounded, deeply concave.
</paragraph>
